---
By: Tarthang Tulku
Locus:
  Page: 383
  Verse: 10
Tags:
  - Problems
---
When a child encounters something he does not want, he has all kinds of
maneuvers to avoid it, such as crying, hiding or fighting. ...Unless we are
taught to face our problems directly and work through them, the pattern of
avoidance will be repeated. ...it can be a natural, accepted way to act.
